        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39594",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "use method Zend_Log:>setEventItem();\r\n{code}\r\n$log->setEventItem('timestamp', $date);\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-26T20:37:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-26T20:37:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39595",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tubularbell",
                        "name": "tubularbell",
                        "displayName": "Sander Bol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The proposed workaround-solution is not sufficient, as it sets the timestamp to a fixed value, instead of an up-to-date value for every log event being written. \r\n\r\nAlso, while I appreciate that it is possible to work around this problem, I believe the component should work properly, instead of having each and every programmer that wants to use it solve this issue themselves.\r\n\r\nBecause of this, I'm reopening the issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tubularbell",
                        "name": "tubularbell",
                        "displayName": "Sander Bol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-27T00:53:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-27T00:53:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39598",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Sander\r\nIn ZF 1.10.0 was added to the parameter $ extras in Zend_Log::log().\r\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/code\/viewrep\/Zend_Framework\/standard\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Log.php?r1=17687&r2=19493\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$log->info('Message', array('timestamp' => $date));\r\n$log->log('Message', Zend_Log::INFO, array('timestamp' => $date));\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-27T04:37:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-27T05:41:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39603",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tubularbell",
                        "name": "tubularbell",
                        "displayName": "Sander Bol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks Ramon! That's the workaround I initially used, but it breaks when other people had to work with the code as they didn't know about having to make this special exception just because we use Zend_Log_Writer_Db in combination with MySQL.\r\n\r\nI am working on my own implementation of http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/browse\/ZF-181 to help solve this issue, by having Zend_Log_Writer_Db pass a Zend_Date or PHP Date object to the log writer, and enabling the DB adapter to accept that, but it's not moving along very much.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tubularbell",
                        "name": "tubularbell",
                        "displayName": "Sander Bol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-27T08:13:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-27T08:13:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43987",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "With ZF\\-1.11.x was added Zend_Log::setTimestampFormat() \r\nor if you want working Zend_Date you can extend the class \"Zend_Log\" and override Zend_Log::_packEvent(). ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-01-09T18:22:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-01-09T18:22:31.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
